entry.title: Bards Dispense Profanity Game
entry.summary:
Vendor: Why So Ever
Type: Game
Price: 28.00

The judge presents a yellow card, your fellow kitchen-table thespians respond, and before you know it, you've got "If music be the food of ill-shaped fishes, play on". A laugh-till-you-cry look at the Bard's smutty side, the raunchy hilarity of this game knows no bounds. Invented by an English professor and his students, this adult card game asks the low-brow literary question, "To be profane, or not to be?" It includes 100 mock-serious questions for our time and 375 responses drawn word-for-word from the works of William Shakespeare. For four or more over-educated adult players only. Designed by Tim Cassedy, Chelsea Grogan, Jenna Peck, and Kate Petsche. Made in Texas.

entry.summary:

Type: Game

You have to pick your battles, but sometimes the key to winning them is all in the wrist. Whether it's 3D Tic-Tac-Toe or H-O-R-S-E, this set invites you to try your hand (and your luck) at a variety of ping pong play by bouncing balls into the wooden grid. Easy to learn, this showdown of orange versus white balls offers bounce after bounce of fast-paced fun and dozens of ways to battle, including Alphabet Soup, Nine Cup, Level Out, and more. It's a great game of skill and strategy for tailgating or family game nights. Made in China.

entry.title: Darwin's Dinosaur Egg Puzzle
entry.summary:
Vendor: UncommonGoods
Type: Puzzle
Price: 21.00

Evolve your brain power with the Darwin's Dinosaur Egg puzzle. This brain-teasing puzzle from the Great Minds series will test your mental mettle as you attempt to rebuild the egg from its pieces. Perfect for anyone in your life with a vivid imagination and an active mind, this puzzle is inspired by Charles Darwin, whose theory of natural selection revolutionized how we think about our origins and still sparks controversy to this day.

Each puzzle reflects an aspect of the "Great Mind" who inspired it, as well as a brief history of their life and achievements, combining learning and play. An ideal gift for any science whiz or history maven, keep this alluring brain teaser out in the open—it'll attract and keep the attention of your friends! Made in China.

Designed to engage the psyche, the Great Minds series brings together intellectually stimulating puzzles with some of the greatest thinkers from throughout history. Vendor: UncommonGoods

It's not that Zip Zap doesn't like the company of other monsters, he just prefers the peace and quiet of solo activities like kite flying and strolling in the park. If it wasn't for him, the town train wouldn't run on time, and no one would enjoy his grandiose tales like The Mutant and the Behemoth.

To an adult, these are whimsical wooden blocks, but to a child, this is Zip Zap: the nap loving, story telling monster. Your little one can mix and match Zip Zap's magnetic body parts to suit his various duties, from train conducting to time traveling. He'll stick by your small fry (and to fridges, washing machines, and spoons) through every imaginary adventure. Made from sustainably harvested wood and non-toxic materials in Honduras.
